post_text:
Beat the summer heat in Arizona with these four tips:
1. Block out the sunlight in your home by closing the blinds and the drapes.
2. Use fans!
3. Time your cooking and baking for early in the morning or late at night when the temps are cooler outside.
4. Eat ice cream!

1. Block out the sunlight in your home by closing the blinds and the drapes.
2. Use fans!
3. Time your cooking and baking for early in the morning or late at night when the temps are cooler outside.
4. Eat ice cream!

post_text:
Cowtown S.K.A.T.E., a nonprofit organization, serving skateboarding and community, is bringing back its Skateboard Angels Program this holiday season with a goal to donate more than 500 skateboards to deserving Arizona youth.

Last year, Intelli students received skateboards through this program. Please help us support them in helping get skateboards out there this holiday season.

To become a Skateboard Angel and give the gift of skateboarding, visit any of Cowtown Skateboards’ four Valley locations or visit cowtownskateboards.com to donate a skateboard at the discounted price of $54.95 by December 31.

post_text: It's Friday!! IntelliSchool teachers and staff are just trying to stay alive as they wrap up two weeks of training prior to the first day of school (next Wednesday). Yesterday, they trained on procedures to help create a safe school environment. Thank you, Dr. Janet Boberg (Glendale Fire Department) and Officer Alex Waldron (Glendale Police Department) for all of the great information you shared. Check out this video of Dr. Boberg demonstrating lifesaving Continuous Chest Compressions, maintaining the proper beat of the compressions with the music of "Stayin' Alive." Terrific!

post_text: Welcome back, IntelliSchool students and families. The first day of school is next Wednesday, August 16. The first open house of the school year is next Tuesday, August 15. All sites will be open from 10 a.m. - 6 p.m. with a special focus on the hours from 4 p.m. - 6 p.m. At IntelliSchool - Chandler, visitors will be able to watch a "welcome back" PowerPoint presentation, check out the classroom, meet the staff - AND enjoy a chips, nacho cheese, and salsa station. There will be raffle giveaways including one for an Arizona Cardinals gift bag (cap and shirt). Thank you, Arizona Cardinals, for your support of IntelliSchool - Chandler. See you next week!

post_text: IntelliSchool's "Back to School" open house is next Tuesday at all four IntelliSchool sites! From 4 p.m. - 6 p.m., IntelliSchool - PV students and their families will be able to enjoy Mexican mini items, chips and salsa, water and soda, all while viewing a Title I slide show and a senior slide show. They will also be able to log into a computer to check out the curriculum and the "Connector," as well as sit down with teachers and staff to discuss graduation plans, classes, and all things related to earning that high school diploma. Wow! That's a lot of action! See you next Tuesday.

post_text: Open House Day is right around the corner - next Tuesday, August 15th, - at all four IntelliSchool sites. IntelliSchool - Metro will have something for everyone, from 10 a.m. - 6 p.m. New students will be able to find out everything about the classroom and their teachers, while learning about behavior expectations, dress code, and all of the things new students wonder about before the first day of school. Returning students and their families will be able to discuss progress from last year, as well as individual and site goals for the coming year. The IntelliSchool popcorn machine - always a big hit! - will be churning out the popcorn and light refreshments will also be served. Don't forget the first day of school is August 16th. We can't wait to see you.
